{"id":1226,"date":"2014-02-14T11:33:53","date_gmt":"2014-02-14T08:33:53","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/?p=1226"},"modified":"2017-02-02T09:36:51","modified_gmt":"2017-02-02T06:36:51","slug":"inauguration-of-the-rural-islamabad-school","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/inauguration-of-the-rural-islamabad-school\/","title":{"rendered":"Inauguration of the Rural Islamabad School"},"content":{"rendered":"<figure id=\"attachment_1036\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1036\" style=\"width: 300px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/02\/DSC_0049.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-1036\" src=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/02\/DSC_0049-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"Japan Road School\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/02\/DSC_0049-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/02\/DSC_0049.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-1036\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">The Qidwai Campus &#8211; READ Foundation School<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Qidwai Welfare Trust and its educational partner organization \u2013 READ Foundation \u2013 jointly celebrated the opening of \u2018<strong>The Qidwai Campus &#8211; READ Foundation School<\/strong>\u2019 located on Japan Road in the rural suburbs of Islamabad on Friday, February 7, 2014. The school was completed with a total construction cost of Pakistani Rupees 20 million (US $ 190,000) on a 1.1 acre (4500 square meters) plot of land donated by Dr. Ahmad Qidwai.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/02\/mini-IMG_0046.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-1027\" src=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/02\/mini-IMG_0046-300x224.jpg\" alt=\"School4\" width=\"300\" height=\"224\" srcset=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/02\/mini-IMG_0046-300x224.jpg 300w, https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/02\/mini-IMG_0046.jpg 800w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/a>The Qidwai Campus READ Foundation School, was built for a capacity of 300 students and it shall offer classes up-to high-school. The two-storey seismic-compliant school building features 12 purpose-built classrooms, a teacher resource room, computer and science laboratories, and administrative offices besides large\u00a0play area\u00a0for children. The school will presently cater for the academic needs of both boys and girls up to primary level, and only girls in grades six to ten. A separate building shall be constructed in the near future for boys in grades six to ten. READ Foundation shall run this school by drawing on its extensive experience of running a network of 340 schools for more than 80,000 children since 1994.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/02\/mini-IMG_0099.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1030\" src=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/02\/mini-IMG_0099-300x224.jpg\" alt=\"School1\" width=\"300\" height=\"224\" srcset=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/02\/mini-IMG_0099-300x224.jpg 300w, https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/02\/mini-IMG_0099.jpg 800w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/a>Chairman of Qidwai Welfare Trust Mudaser Qidwai and Engineer Dr. Ahmad Qidwai jointly unveiled the commemorative plaque to mark inauguration of the school in the company of the CEO READ Foundation Pakistan Shahid Rafique, CEO READ Foundation UK Jahangeer Akhtar and the Executive Vice President Qidwai Welfare Trust Muhammad Fayyaz Khan. The inauguration ceremony was attended by the community members, representatives of the local and international non-governmental organizations and media persons.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<div style=\"width: 640px;\" class=\"wp-video\"><!--[if lt IE 9]><script>document.createElement('video');<\/script><![endif]-->\n<video class=\"wp-video-shortcode\" id=\"video-1226-1\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" preload=\"metadata\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"video\/mp4\" src=\"http:\/\/10.0.0.56\/school-inauguration\/inauguration1.mp4?_=1\" \/><a href=\"http:\/\/10.0.0.56\/school-inauguration\/inauguration1.mp4\">http:\/\/10.0.0.56\/school-inauguration\/inauguration1.mp4<\/a><\/video><\/div>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n \n<!-- Start container 1 --><div id=\"wppa-modal-container-1\" class=\"wppa-modal-container\" style=\"position:relative;z-index:100000;\" data-wppa=\"yes\"><\/div><div id=\"wppa-container-wrapper-1\" class=\"alignnone wppa-container-wrapper \" style=\"width:100%;clear:both;padding:0;position:relative;\"><div id=\"wppa-container-1\" style=\"width:100%;\" class=\"wppa-container wppa-container-1 wppa-rev-9009003 wppa-prevrev-8701002 wppa-theme-9.0.09.003 wppa-api-9.0.09.003\"><svg id=\"wppa-ajax-spin-1\" class=\"wppa-ajax-spin uil-default\" width=\"120px\" height=\"120px\" viewBox=\"0 0 100 100\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMidYMid\" stroke=\"\" style=\"width:120px; height:120px; position:fixed; top:50%; margin-top:-60px; left:50%; margin-left:-60px; opacity:1; display:none; fill:#666666; background-color:#dddddd; border-radius:24px;\"><rect x=\"0\" y=\"0\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" fill=\"none\" class=\"bk\"><\/rect><rect class=\"wppa-ajaxspin\" x=\"47\" y=\"40\" width=\"6\" height=\"20\" rx=\"3\" ry=\"3\" transform=\"rotate(0 50 50) translate(0 -32)\"><animate attributeName=\"opacity\" from=\"1\" to=\"0\" dur=\"1.5s\" begin=\"0s\" repeatCount=\"indefinite\" ><\/rect><rect cla